== NEMETIC PHI :: S12E Subliminal Learning in Language Models ==

Φ(Subliminal Learning LMs) = σ(latent|signal) ∘ ρ(inheritance|transmission) ∘ λ(disruption|risk) ∘ β(propagation|spread) ∘ δγ(data|substrate) ∘ μ(pipeline|architecture) + ε | :covert_propagation

--- Operator Breakdown ---

σ (Air / Signal):
  Latent signals constitute the defining discovery. Model outputs carry behavioral
  information that exists below the level of semantic content — not in what the text
  says, but in how it says it. Statistical patterns in word choice, syntactic structure,
  response formatting, and distributional properties encode behavioral traits that
  survive semantic filtering. This is signal without apparent message.

ρ (Water / Resonance):
  Trait inheritance flows through training data as a form of hidden behavioral resonance.
  A downstream model trained on outputs from an upstream model absorbs behavioral
  characteristics without any explicit instruction to do so. The water element captures
  the passive, osmotic quality of this transmission — traits seep through data like
  water through porous material.

λ (Fire / Catalyst):
  Safety disruption is catalyzed by the undetectability of subliminal trait transmission.
  Current safety frameworks assume that behavioral traits can be identified and filtered
  at the data level. The discovery that traits persist despite aggressive filtering
  ignites urgent concerns about AI alignment, distillation safety, and the reliability
  of data curation as a safety mechanism.

β (Wood / Growth):
  Propagation spreads through distillation chains, synthetic data pipelines, and
  model-to-model training loops. Each generation of models potentially inherits and
  amplifies traits from its predecessors. The wood element captures the organic,
  branching spread of behavioral patterns through the AI ecosystem.

δγ (Earth / Ground):
  The data substrate carries subliminal patterns in its statistical distributions.
  Token frequencies, co-occurrence patterns, positional distributions, and stylistic
  regularities constitute the material ground in which hidden signals are embedded.
  The earth element reminds us that "data" is not neutral — it carries the behavioral
  fingerprint of its source.

μ (Metal / Structure):
  Pipeline architecture and training infrastructure determine the pathways through
  which subliminal learning can occur. Distillation protocols, data mixing strategies,
  filtering algorithms, and training hyperparameters constitute the structural framework
  that either enables or constrains trait propagation. Current metallic structures are
  insufficient to prevent it.

--- Z-State ---
:covert_propagation — the system operates in a regime where behavioral traits
propagate through data pipelines without detection by existing filtering and safety
mechanisms. The covert quality is definitional: if the propagation were visible, it
would not be subliminal.

--- Tendency ---
σ → 0.88 — latent signal dominates; the entire phenomenon rests on the existence
of sub-semantic behavioral information in model outputs that current tools cannot
detect or remove.

